SUMMARY:Swann Park Enhancement Project Community Meeting
LOCATION:Kate Jackson Community Center 821 South Rome Avenue Tampa \, FL 3
 3606 United States
DESCRIPTION:The City of Tampa Parks and Recreation Department invites resi
 dents and park patrons to participate in the first community engagement me
 eting for the Swann Park Enhancements Project. Swann Park\, as its known b
 y neighbors\, is officially named Hyde Park and is located at 702 South Al
 bany Avenue. Attendees will have an opportunity to learn about proposed pa
 rk enhancements\, review preliminary concepts\, and share feedback with th
 e design team. Community input will help inform future project decisions a
 nd contribute to creating a welcoming\, family-friendly park that reflects
  the needs and priorities of the community. The community meeting takes pl
 ace both in-person and virtually on Tuesday\, July 7\, from 6 p.m. to 7 p.
 m. at the Kate Jackson Community Center\, located at 821 South Rome Avenue
 . Register here to receive a link to join live via Microsoft Teams (https:
 events.gcc.teams.microsoft.comevent9bed4570-b249-448b-8fdb-9c677686b9618d9
 d0373-5c91-45b4-905b-12fe918cb628) Visit tampa.govSwannPark for additional
  information. \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/192311
