SUMMARY:Sacred Heart Catholic Church
LOCATION:509 N. Florida Avenue Tampa \, FL 33602 United States
DESCRIPTION:Please join the docents of the Sacred Heart Historical Society
  as they give you a verbal history and tour of the oldest Catholic church 
 on Floridas West Coast. Learn about the oldest\, continually operational p
 arish in central Florida\, which dates to the pioneer days of Tampa. Then 
 how in 1888\, its congregation survived the tragic loss of three priests d
 ue to yellow fever. They then built one of the oldest structures in downto
 wn Tampa. Also\, learn about the architect who designed the church but nev
 er set foot in the building. Plus much more! \n\nPermalink: https://www.ta
 mpa.gov/node/192146
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/192146
