SUMMARY:Back To School Health Clinic - Central
LOCATION:4401 N. Himes Ave. Tampa \, FL 33614 United States
DESCRIPTION:The Back-2-School Health Clinics are returning this summer to 
 help families across Hillsborough County prepare for the new school year. 
 The clinics provide no-cost school physicals\, routine immunizations\, and
  Florida Form DH 680 immunization record transfersservices that are essent
 ial for school enrollment. A non-refundable 10 registration fee is require
 d per family (not per child). Medical services are available by appointmen
 t only for children who are uninsured\, underinsured\, or enrolled in Medi
 caid. The clinics are designed to serve students entering Kindergarten\, e
 ntering 7th grade\, or those who are NEW to Hillsborough County Public or 
 Charter Schools in any grade level. Clinics will be held every Saturday fr
 om July 11 through August 8\, 2026\, at six convenient locations throughou
 t Hillsborough County. Space is limited\, and walk-ins cannot be accommoda
 ted. Families are encouraged to register early at www.b2shc.org. Start the
  school year strong by ensuring your child is healthy\, protected\, and re
 ady to learn! \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/192026
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/192026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:bb404e3c-6b0e-4ca2-9e60-a9b3ba8155a3
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260708T002001Z
DTSTART:20260808T180000Z
DTEND:20260808T220000Z
SUMMARY:Annual Tampa Noles Block Party
LOCATION:1731 East 7th Avenue Tampa \, FL 33605 United States
DESCRIPTION:Overview The annual Tampa Noles Block Party returns to histori
 c Ybor City on Saturday\, August 8\, 2026! Join us on Saturday\, August 8\
 , 2026 for the Tampa Bay Seminole Clubs annual Block Party fundraiser in h
 istoric Ybor City! Kick off football season with thousands of your fellow 
 Noles while supporting local establishments\, enjoying FSU themed drink sp
 ecials\, and giving back to our local community. Proceeds from ticket sale
 s benefit full-ride scholarships to FSU students from the Tampa Bay area. 
 Go Noles! Ticket Options: General Admission : General admission allows acc
 ess into all participating venues beginning at 2PM. Complimentary food swa
 g\, cash bar and vendors will be available on the first floor of the Itali
 an Club while supplies last. Must pick up wristband at Italian Club before
  entering venues. VIP : The VIP experience includes: Early access beginnin
 g at 12:30PM Private lounge access on the third floor of the Italian Club\
 , including VIP air conditioned restrooms Complimentary unlimited premium 
 bar and catered food Swag from Tampa Noles and other localFSU affiliated v
 endors Entry into exclusive raffles for items like game day tickets Silent
  auction Live DJ Special guests like the Marching Chiefs Alumni Band and m
 ore! Please note: This is a private\, ticketed event. Attendees must be 21
  years of age to attend and must have an official Tampa Noles Block Party 
 wristband in order to enter any participating venues\, receive special off
 ers or claim prizes. No refunds. Rain or shine! Questions? Please contact 
 infotampanoles.com. \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/192041
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/192041
END:VEVENT
